    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="22"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51 Manchuria/33</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France (<persName type="from"
                            >Edge</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 3231</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-06">January 6,
                            1933</date>.<lb/>[Received January 13.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s Instruction No.
                    1471 of December 14, 1932,<note n="29" xml:id="d22fn29">Not printed; for its
                        enclosures, see memoranda of November 30 and December 6, 1932, <ref
                            target="frus1932v04#pg_377">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1932, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, pp. 377</ref> and <ref
                            target="frus1932v04#pg_390">390</ref>.</note> relating to the report
                    that a consortium of Japanese banks had decided to make a loan of 30 million yen
                    to Manchoukuo, I have the honor to report that a member of the Embassy staff has
                    been assured in informal conversations with officials of the Finance Ministry
                    that the question raised has not been brought to the attention of the
                    Ministry.</p>
                <p>The matter will be carefully watched and any information that the Embassy is able
                    to gather concerning it will be reported promptly to the Department.</p>
                <p>Yours respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Walter E. Edge</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
